      <textAnnotation id="sid-5142449E-CE8F-4199-A6C9-1C1383926255" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Process Tower: Procure To Pay
Process Group: Procure Materials and Services (Direct &amp; Indirect)
Process: P-150-170 Identify Optimum Timing for Payment</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-F04D54E9-5FA0-4B25-BEF2-219419DF2078" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Invoice due date will be calculated based on Baseline data and Payment term</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-76C6C119-3BEF-4176-809C-E4375E181526" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Payment blocks allowing a single invoice to be split into multiple payments and have future amounts blocked, so that the invoice can be paid at different points in time.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-EDC21656-5711-4E1B-B015-C23898E32CA1" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Block an invoice where services or goods were procured from a foreign supplier, if it needs be stopped for CDS (Custom Declaration Sheet) block so the invoice can be stopped until appropriate additional documentation can be provided.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-F82FD17E-5C33-41E7-AD31-B8F450F39186" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>For China only, all invoices with WHT are blocked and Intel has been approved by gov't tax agency to manually calculate the WHT and remove the block without needing to receive the WHT certificate.

If it has been determined to have over $50k of withholding tax, the invoice remains blocked until the withholding tax certificate is provided by the government tax agency.</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-AEE960A8-66ED-4D5A-B4E9-3E7BC43AEB1A" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Manual Payment Block on the SAP Accounting Document for a posted Invoice or Credit Memo in the S4 system to prevent the document from being captured by the automated payment run (currently using Payment Block - B)</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-DB5FCF20-E495-4FA0-9FB8-2A71E125610B" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>1. Payment term is pulled from the originating document (PO, Contract, NonPO Tool upload, eCheck submission)
2. Processor can overwrite the payment term detail in the invoice</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-09475ED5-0A18-4F94-8706-6A3BA5928F0F" signavio:alignment="left" textFormat="text/plain">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioMetaData metaKey="bordercolor" metaValue="#000000"/>
         </extensionElements>
         <text>Based on business scenario, invoice can be blocked manually or automatically</text>
      </textAnnotation>
      <textAnnotation id="sid-3EDF0FE3-2884-4054-887B-14A1304867E9" signavio:alignment="left">
         <extensionElements>
            <signavio:signavioDictionaryLink propertyId="name">
